# De Bruijn grf feladat - Prob2Mod
# 1. Alap feladat az eladson elhangzottak alapjn

G = DiGraph([[str(bin(i))[2:].zfill(3) for i in range(8)], []], loops = true)
for u in G.vertices():
    for v in G.vertices():
        if u[1:] == v[:-1]:
            G.add_edge(u, v, u + v[-1])

print("\nBemeneti szavak B(2, 3) esetn:")
print(f"\n {G.vertices()} \n")

print("\nA bemeneti szavakbl alkothat De Brujn grf:")
G.show(talk = true, edge_labels = true, figsize = 7.5)

elements = [v[0] for v in G.eulerian_circuit() if v[0] != v[1]]
text = elements[0]
for e in elements[1:]:
    if e not in text:
        text += e[-1:]
print("\nA bemenetbl alkothat De Bruijn sz:")
print(f"\n '{text}' \n")

Bemeneti szavak B(2, 3) esetn:

 ['000', '001', '010', '011', '100', '101', '110', '111'] 


A bemeneti szavakbl alkothat De Brujn grf:

A bemenetbl alkothat De Bruijn sz:

 '0001110100'

#2. Ktbets ABC 5 hossz szavakkal B(2, 5)
#Paramterezhet fggvny (n, k)

def convert2base(n, b):
    #segdfgggvny szm konverzihoz
    q, r = divmod(n, b)
    number = f"{r}"
    while q != 0:
        q, r = divmod(q, b)
        number += str(r)
    return number[::-1]

def deBruijn(n, k):
    G = DiGraph([[str(convert2base(i, n)).zfill(k) for i in range(n**k)], []], loops = true)
    for u in G.vertices():
        for v in G.vertices():
            if u[1:] == v[:-1]:
                G.add_edge(u, v, u + v[-1])
    print("\nBemeneti szavak:")
    print(f"\n {G.vertices()} \n")
    print("\nA bemeneti szavakbl alkothat De Brujn grf:")

    G.show(talk = true, edge_labels = true, vertex_size = 50, figsize = 25, layout = 'circular')

    elements = [v[0] for v in G.eulerian_circuit() if v[0] != v[1]]
    text = elements[0]
    for e in elements[1:]:
        if e not in text:
            text += e[-1:]
    print("\nA bemenetbl alkothat De Bruijn sz:")
    print(f"\n '{text}' \n")

deBruijn(2, 5)

Bemeneti szavak:

 ['00000', '00001', '00010', '00011', '00100', '00101', '00110', '00111', '01000', '01001', '01010', '01011', '01100', '01101', '01110', '01111', '10000', '10001', '10010', '10011', '10100', '10101', '10110', '10111', '11000', '11001', '11010', '11011', '11100', '11101', '11110', '11111'] 


A bemeneti szavakbl alkothat De Brujn grf:

A bemenetbl alkothat De Bruijn sz:

 '0000011111011011001011101001010010010000'

#3. Grf brk
#inspirci forrsa: https://hu.wikipedia.org/wiki/De_Bruijn-gr%C3%A1f

def convert2base(n, b):
    #segdfgggvny szm konverzihoz
    q, r = divmod(n, b)
    number = f"{r}"
    while q != 0:
        q, r = divmod(q, b)
        number += str(r)
    return number[::-1]

def deBruijnDraw(n, k):
    G = DiGraph([[str(convert2base(i, n)).zfill(k) for i in range(n**k)], []], loops = true)
    for u in G.vertices():
        for v in G.vertices():
            if u[1:] == v[:-1] and u != v and not G.has_edge(u, v):
                G.add_edge(u, v, u + v[-1])

    G.to_undirected().graphplot(vertex_labels = false,
                                vertex_size = 0,
                                edge_color = 'chocolate',
                                edge_thickness = 0.125,
                                layout = 'circular').show()

deBruijnDraw(2, 8)
deBruijnDraw(3, 5)
deBruijnDraw(4, 4)
In[84]:
deBruijnDraw(5, 3)
